SIMPLE: stiffen
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stiffen
<hw>Stiff"en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Stiffened</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Stiffening</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[See
<er>Stiff</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To make stiff; to make less
pliant or flexible; <as>as, to <ex>stiffen</ex> cloth with
starch</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Stiffen</qex> the sinews, summon up the blood.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To inspissate; to make more thick or viscous;
<as>as, to <ex>stiffen</ex> paste</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To make torpid; to benumb.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stiffen</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Stiffen
<hw>Stiff"en</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To become stiff or stiffer, in
any sense of the adjective.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Like bristles rose my <qex>stiffening</qex> hair.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The tender soil then <qex>stiffening</qex> by degrees.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some souls we see,⟦br⟧
Grow hard and <qex>stiffen</qex> with adversity.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stiffener</ent>⟦br⟧
